cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with 3D reconstruction from a single view image using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method focuses on reconstructing complex 3D mesh models with fine details, which suggests the paper may also belong to the graphics sub-category (cs.GR). The use of deep learning techniques for shape representation and reconstruction also suggests the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experimental results involve images, which suggests the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
